Topics Reviewed
Network Segmentation

Jump Hosts / Security Zones

Used to control administrative access to sensitive environments.

Reduces exposure by isolating internal systems from direct external access.

Data Protection Techniques

Data Masking / Obfuscation

Protects sensitive data by replacing real values with altered data.

Prevents exposure of personally identifiable information.

Virtualization Security

Escape to Host Attacks

Occur when attackers break out of a VM or container environment.

Allows access to the underlying host system.

Social Engineering Threats

Tailgating

Unauthorized individual gains access by following an authorized user into a restricted area.

Vishing

Voice-based phishing attack conducted via phone calls.

Attackers impersonate trusted entities to obtain sensitive information.

Security Monitoring

SIEM

Aggregates and correlates logs from multiple sources.

Improves visibility into security events and potential incidents.

Vulnerability Prioritization

CVSS (Common Vulnerability Scoring System)

Provides standardized vulnerability severity scoring.

Helps organizations prioritize remediation based on impact and exploitability.

Insider Threat Detection

Behavioral Analytics

Monitors user behavior patterns.

Detects deviations that may indicate malicious or compromised insider activity.

Network Traffic Monitoring

Firewall Logs

Track inbound and outbound traffic.

Useful for identifying command-and-control communication attempts from compromised devices.

